translation.en: Get back here, you little hubcap! It's…
[Mama] All right, you've got nowhere to go!
Let's all just go home and take a nice, warm bath.
translation.es: Vamos a casa a darnos un baño caliente.

translation.en: Stay on her tail. I'll cut her off at the pass!
Huh? Why aren't you in school?
I got ya! I got ya! I…
You fall for that every time.
Another peaceful day in Bumperton Hills.
Come on. It's your turn to take a bath.
Maybe you could teach Chrissy to love baths too.
Choppy water, choppy water, choppy water.
[gasps] I know! Close your eyes and pretend real hard.
translation.es: ¡Ya sé! Cierra los ojos y usa la imaginación.

translation.en: Hey, Chrissy. You look so cute bouncing on that trampoline.
translation.es: Chrissy, te ves muy tierna en la cama elástica.

translation.en: Of course. Chrissy. You are just the cutest thing ever!
translation.es: Claro. Eres lo más tierno del mundo.

translation.en: What you doin'? Blowin' dandelions? Makin' wishes?
translation.es: ¿Qué haces? ¿Soplando dientes de león por deseos?

translation.en: You are just the cutest thing ever!
-[Bobby blowing] -Keep trying, little guy. You can do it.
Looks like someone needs some holdin'.
Oh, I-- I don't know that song.
Uh, this is all so very cute.
[Carley] That is the cutest thing ever!
translation.es: ¡Eso es lo más tierno del mundo!

translation.en: Well, you see, my dad was gonna throw it out, but I saved it.
translation.es: Mi papá iba a tirarla, pero la rescaté.

translation.en: Because it reminded me of you.
Wanna go help me add it to my gallery space?
translation.es: ¿Me ayudas a ponerla en mi galería?

translation.en: Here you go, Chrissy. I got you a special treat.
Nice try, but raisins are good for you,
and makes Mommy feel better about that milkshake I gave you yesterday.
translation.es: y mamá se sentirá mejor por la malteada de ayer.

translation.en: Chasing a cookie in a jar, I see.
translation.es: Persigues una galleta en un frasco.

translation.en: I remember the first time I chased a sugary snack.
translation.es: Recuerdo la primera vez que perseguí un dulce.

translation.en: Fastest crumb cake I ever-- Don't mean to be rude, but I'm going left. Bye!
translation.es: El pastel más rápido… No por grosero, pero me voy. ¡Adiós!

translation.en: Hey, kids. Who wants a healthy snack?
I-- I don't have any cookies!
Please don't eat me! I'm not as sweet as I look!
translation.es: ¡Por favor, no me comas! ¡No soy tan dulce como parezco!

translation.en: You ate all your raisins! Good job, Chrissy.
I think you deserve a cookie.

translation.es: La última de avena con pasas.

translation.en: ♪ Baby Unicar! Colors so bright! Travels the uni-- ♪
Now, you know we don't draw on the wall…
translation.es: Sabes que no dibujamos en la pared…

translation.en: [blubbers] No. No drawing on the wall.
That is not what I meant! Chrissy, I'm warning you.
translation.es: ¡No te ordené eso! Te lo advierto.

translation.en: Okay, you need to stay on the couch until time out is over.
translation.es: Te quedas en el sofá hasta que se acabe el castigo.

translation.en: I'm setting this timer for five minutes.
You can get up when the face goes from sad to happy.
translation.es: Hasta que la cara pase de triste a feliz.

translation.en: I'll be just in the other room.
♪ Travels the universe Making wrongs right ♪
translation.es: Viaja por el universo Haciendo lo correcto

translation.en: Stay on the couch until time out is over.
translation.es: Hasta que se acabe el castigo.

translation.en: [gasps] Oh no! No TV during time outs.
translation.es: - ¡No! - No hay TV durante los castigos.

translation.en: Well, at least it comes off easy.

translation.es: Mi baúl no es tan grande.

translation.en: -No, you see, Chrissy, I was just-- -That's it! Time out!
Don't leave couch until sad to happy.
translation.es: No bajes hasta que la cara pase a feliz.

translation.en: Uh, Chrissy, you set it for an hour.
-[Mama] Where to next, everybody? -Last one to the ball pit's a rusty car!
translation.es: ¿Adónde ahora? El último es un auto oxidado.

translation.en: Are you two eyeing that big Baby Unicar toy?
One hundred tickets is a lot,
but it's worth it 'cause it's our last one.
translation.es: pero lo vale porque es el último.

translation.en: Last chance to bring your tickets in to exchange them for a prize!
Hey, you two. What prizes can I get you today?
translation.es: Hola a ambos. ¿Qué premios les daré hoy?

translation.en: Whoa! Okay. I'm gonna go count these up.
Sorry, guys. You both only have 50 tickets each. Pencils are all you can get.
translation.es: Lo siento, cada uno tiene 50 boletos. Para eso alcanza.

translation.en: Maybe if you put your tickets together,
translation.es: Tal vez, si juntan sus boletos,

translation.en: you could share the Baby Unicar toy?
Chrissy best hide and seeker. -She is pretty good. -Mm-hmm.
translation.es: - Soy la mejor en esto. - Es buena.

translation.en: Well, we'll see who's the best.
Now it's my turn to seek and I'm gonna find you all in no time.
translation.es: Mi turno de buscarlos y los hallaré enseguida.

translation.en: Chrissy, if I can't find you, you can have cookies for dinner.
translation.es: Si no te encuentro, puedes cenar galletas.

translation.en: Ready or not, here I come!
Come out, come out, wherever you are!
-I thought you'd never find me here. -[Papa chuckles]
-If we split up, we can cover more ground. -Good idea.
translation.es: - Si nos separamos, abarcamos más terreno. - Sí.

translation.en: -[Cory] It came from the closet! -Chrissy, they're coming!
[scoffs] Looks like they found us, Chrissy.
Looks like Chrissy's better than you thought.
translation.es: Es mejor de lo que creías.

translation.en: What? She just got lucky! We'll find her.
-What? -Freddie, why are you in my house?
I'm playing hide and seek with Kimmy and Timmy. They'll never find me here.
translation.es: Juego escondidas con Kimmy y Timmy. No me hallarán aquí.

translation.en: -What should we do? -I don't know where else to look.
Okay, you win! Chrissy, you're the best at hide and seek!
translation.es: ¡Bien, tú ganas! Eres la mejor en las escondidas.

translation.en: Whoa, you keep jumping like that and there won't be any water left!
translation.es: ¡Sigue saltando así y no quedará agua!

translation.en: Time to head home, Chrissy. Say goodbye to Catalina.
translation.es: Hora de volver. Despídete de Catalina.

translation.en: Okay, just one more. I'm gonna say goodbye to Cat's mom.
translation.es: Solo una más. Voy a despedirme de la mamá de Cat.

translation.en: Those kids just love being in the water.
translation.es: Les encanta estar en el agua.

translation.en: -Nice circle! -How are we gonna make this triangle?
Can we please have crumpets for dinner?
-All right, see you next week. -See you then.
translation.es: - Hasta la otra semana. - Nos vemos.

translation.en: [Papa] Hmm, now it just needs a really funny joke.
translation.es: Solo le falta un buen chiste.

translation.en: Let's see what's on the internet.
translation.es: A ver qué hay en Internet.

translation.en: [Papa] ♪ A great idea will come to me ♪
translation.es: Se me ocurrirá una gran idea

translation.en: Ooh, someone commented on my new profile pic!
I should probably take a power nap before lunch.
Get off my bumper, Bobby. Are we doing it or not?
translation.es: No seas molesto, Bobby. ¿Lo haremos o no?

translation.en: [Mama] …additional concrete to support the new structure.
Oh, hold on, Julia, I need to take this call.
Hi, hon, it's me, Papa. Have you seen my snuggle socks?
translation.es: Hola, cariño, soy papá. ¿Viste mis calcetines?

translation.en: Top drawer. Wait, are you about to take a nap?
translation.es: Primer cajón. ¿Vas a dormir una siesta?

translation.en: I'm back. Let's open the blueprints and take a look at the foundation.
translation.es: Ya volví. Abramos los planos y veamos los cimientos.

translation.en: One and a two and a three, four, five.
[grunts] You're getting so big. Don't you grow up too fast, okay?
translation.es: Te estás poniendo grande. No crezcas tan rápido, ¿sí?

translation.en: -Wait. Did you just wink at yourself? -Yep.
I just need to draw a perfectly straight line.
translation.es: Solo necesito trazar una línea recta.

translation.en: Ah! Oh, Chrissy. You scared me.
Do you have a case of the hiccups?
I have just the thing. Drink some water.
Oh, I know. Let's try this.
Now take a drink of water.
I'm just helping Chrissy cure her hiccups.
translation.es: Ayudo a Chrissy a curar su hipo.

translation.en: Oh. Well, I have an idea.
My mom always gave me a spoonful of sugar to cure my hiccups.
translation.es: Mi mamá siempre me daba una cucharada de azúcar.

translation.en: I don't know if that'll work.
No, we're just trying to get rid of Chrissy's hiccups.
translation.es: No, intentamos curar el hipo de Chrissy.

translation.en: Oh, my mom has a neat trick for that.
You just have to hold your breath for ten seconds.
-[hiccups] -Oh, Chrissy! Do you have the hiccups?
A good laugh always gets rid of them for me.
translation.es: Una buena risa siempre me lo cura.

translation.en: What do you call a sick train?
The best way to get rid of hiccups is by scaring them away.
translation.es: La mejor manera de curar el hipo es con un susto.

translation.en: When I get the hiccups, I fly corkscrews through the air. That always helps.
translation.es: Cuando tengo hipo, vuelo en espirales. Siempre ayuda.

translation.en: You'll just have to bounce them out.
-My mom gave me a spoonful of sugar-- -Yeah, we tried that.
translation.es: - Mi mamá me daba azúcar… - Sí, lo intentamos.

translation.en: This mask will definitely scare those hiccups out of Chrissy.
translation.es: Esta máscara sí que asustará a Chrissy.

translation.en: I knew laughter would do the trick.
Look at me! Look at me!
Hot chocolate. Get your hot chocolate here!
What a nice day to go sledding.
translation.es: Lindo día para andar en trineo.

translation.en: Whoa, slow down, Chrissy. Wait for me.
Let's go! Let's go! Let's go!
Uh, Chrissy, people say the best part of sledding is actually the view.
translation.es: Dicen que lo mejor de andar en trineo es la vista.

translation.en: Why don't we just stay up here and get some hot chocolate?
translation.es: ¿Y si nos quedamos y compramos chocolate?

translation.en: Chrissy! Wait, wait, wait. No! No! No! No!
[Papa chuckles] You know what? The best part of sledding really is the view.
translation.es: Lo mejor de andar en trineo es la vista.

translation.en: Huh? Sorry, Chrissy, I can't. I have a lot of work to do.
translation.es: Lo siento, tengo mucho trabajo que hacer.

translation.en: Oh, maybe you could go play with Mama and Cory?
translation.es: Podrías ir a jugar con mamá y Cory.

translation.en: -We're actually in the middle of a game. -Yeah, ages five and up.
translation.es: - Estamos jugando un juego. - De cinco años en adelante.

translation.en: -Maybe you can play with Papa? -Papa no play time.
translation.es: - Quizá puedas jugar con papá. - Papá no jugará.

translation.en: It lets you control someone like you control the TV. Watch. Hey, Cory!
translation.es: Controla a alguien como a la televisión. Mira. ¡Oye, Cory!

translation.en: Oh, hey, is that super remote?
But the rule is that you have to play along no matter what. Play!
translation.es: Pero debes seguir el juego sin importar qué. ¡Play!

translation.en: I remember the fun we used to…
Hey! Who put this banana in my card pile?
translation.es: ¿Quién puso esta banana en mis cartas?

translation.en: You never do stuff like that to me, do you?
Just don't use it on me, okay?
Huh? Where did my pencil go?
Very funny, but I need to get back to work.
This comic is gonna take forever to finish.
translation.es: Terminar este cómic me llevará mucho.

translation.en: Done. Bye, Mr. Pencil! I'm hungry. Time for a snack! See you later, Chrissy!
Hi, whatcha doing? Making nachos? None for me. Ketchup. Corn. Pan. No.
translation.es: Hola, ¿qué haces? ¿Nachos? No quiero. Ketchup. Maíz. Pan. No.

translation.en: -Nothing like a cold glass of juice! -Pause.
-You two look like you're having fun. -Mama, play time!
translation.es: - Parece que se divierten. - ¡Mamá, a jugar!

translation.en: I can't. I gotta get back to my game.
translation.es: No, debo volver a mi juego.

translation.en: Looks like I'm in control now.
-Play. Pause. Play. Pause. Play. -Mama, what are you doing?
We're still playing! Papa, do something!
[Cory] Come on, Chrissy. You've had your fun.
Time to get back to work.
Well, I guess no more super remote.

translation.es: Y no más hora de jugar.

translation.en: Look, everyone! It's the saltshaker of madness!
If you get hit by the magic salt,
translation.es: Si te toca la sal mágica,

translation.en: Okay, so I think we have all the resources we need.
translation.es: Creo que tenemos todo lo que necesitamos.

translation.en: I've got some work to do though. Do you think you can take care of it?
translation.es: Tengo trabajo que hacer. ¿Crees que puedas encargarte?

translation.en: All right, I'm back. Let's raid this dungeon!

translation.es: Perfume de camión de Gary Basuras.

translation.en: Guaranteed to make you smell like the greatest garbage truck in the world.
translation.es: Te garantiza oler como el mejor camión de basura del mundo.

translation.en: I wouldn't go in there if I were you.
translation.es: No entraría ahí si fuera tú.

translation.en: I don't know who used the bathroom last,
translation.es: No sé quién usó el baño,

translation.en: but might just be best to, you know, let it air out.
translation.es: pero sería mejor dejar entrar aire.

translation.en: Yeah! We need to use the bathroom!
Hey, Chrissy. I see you found the smell.
translation.es: Hola, Chrissy. Veo que hallaste el olor.

translation.en: I knew you could do it.
Wait. What the… Where's the toilet?
-[dance music] -Welcome to the Lucky Lounge. Here you go, boys.
translation.es: - Bienvenida al Salón de la Suerte. - Tomen.

translation.en: Thank you, Miss Fenderson. Enjoy yourself this evening.

translation.es: - Solo ganadores de muchos boletos. - Boleto.

translation.en: You need more than that if you wanna party with the high rollers.
translation.es: Necesitarás más para festejar con los grandes.

translation.en: [game] Sorry! Too bad! Sorry! Almost! Too bad!
Crispy! Combo! Awesome! Crispy! Combo! Perfect score!
You got a lucky penny. Better hang onto it.
translation.es: Una moneda de la suerte. No la pierdas.

translation.en: Ha! Luck's got nothing to do with it.
I finally got the white whale!
translation.es: ¡Por fin atrapé a la ballena blanca!

translation.en: [announcer] Welcome to the 65th annual Bumper-Ball Championship!
But first, a quick word from our sponsor.
I'm gonna go upstairs and do some work.
-You're gonna take a nap, aren't you? -What? No!
Morning, Chrissy. We're babysitting one of your friends today.
translation.es: Buen día. Hoy cuidaremos a tu amigo.

translation.en: I left a snack for you two on the table!
translation.es: ¡Les dejé un bocadillo en la mesa!

translation.en: We've got the match of the century here today, folks!
It's the long-awaited showdown between two fated rivals.
translation.es: El esperado choque entre estos rivales.

translation.en: The Mean Green Machines versus the Tin Can Vans!
translation.es: ¡Las Máquinas Verdes Malvadas contra las Furgonetas de Lata!

translation.en: Who will take the win? Who will come out on top?
The Tin Can Vans have snatched the ball from the offense.
translation.es: Las Furgonetas roban el balón al ataque.

translation.en: They are headed downfield. Look at that fancy wheel work.
translation.es: Van a campo contrario. Cómo funciona esa rueda.

translation.en: And goal! It's a goal for the Tin Can Vans!
The Mean Greens are left in shock.
But they don't leave them a second to celebrate.
Both teams are scrambling. I can barely see the ball, folks!
translation.es: Toda una lucha. ¡Apenas veo la pelota!

translation.en: It's been found. The Mean Greens have the ball.
We're off to the races! What a beautiful maneuver.
Go, Mean Greens! Show 'em who's boss!

translation.es: Este chico sí que es rápido.

translation.en: Ah-ha! And it's a goal for Green!
The Vans manage to break away! It looks like a clean--
Wait a minute. What just happened?
A fan has come onto the field. He's stolen the ball!
translation.es: ¡Un fan entró y se robó la pelota!

translation.en: Can no one get their tires on the slippery suspect?
Oh, they got him. The fan is down!
They're really giving him a walloping!
The match is heating up. There's no sign of it slowing down.
translation.es: No parece que vayan a bajar la marcha.

translation.en: And those victory dances are nothing to sneeze at.
translation.es: Y esos bailes no son poca cosa.

translation.en: The walls are closing in. There's nowhere left to turn.
translation.es: Las paredes se cierran. No hay dónde ir.

translation.en: But wait! A teammate is wide open. Waiting in the wings like an angel.
A beautiful pass. And beautifully received.
translation.es: Un pase hermoso. Y cómo lo recibió.

translation.en: It's all come down to this. One final goal will decide the match.
translation.es: Todo se reduce a esto. Un gol decidirá el partido.

translation.en: With seconds on the clock, who will take the championship title?
It's another mad scramble. The play goes haywire.
translation.es: Otra pelea. Este juego es una locura.

translation.en: Cars are sent head over wheels.
The ball is in the air. It's anyone's game.
translation.es: Pelota en el aire. Cualquiera gana.

translation.en: It's all over, folks! It's a tie!
Oh, look at you two having so much fun together.
Oh, there's only one left. I'll go get some cups so we can split it.
translation.es: Solo queda uno. Buscaré unas tazas para dividirlo.

translation.en: We wouldn't leave you hanging, folks! The match moves into overtime.
translation.es: ¡Seguimos! El juego va a tiempo extra.

translation.en: Okay. This goes in here. And this…
translation.es: Bien. Esto va aquí. Y esto…

translation.en: Hop on out of that box, please.
translation.es: Sal de la caja, por favor.

translation.en: We used to make home movies of you and Cory with this all the time.
translation.es: Solíamos filmarlos a ti y a Cory con esto.

translation.en: [Papa] Here we go! Hi, Chrissy. Say hi to the camera!
translation.es: ¡Aquí vamos! Hola, Chrissy. ¡Saluda a la cámara!

translation.en: Okay, that was fun. Now I need to get back to--
translation.es: Eso fue divertido. Ahora debo volver a…

translation.en: I just have so much to do.
[Papa] Yeah. There's Cory, walking down the hill. Hi, Cory! Where's Chrissy?
translation.es: Cory está bajando la colina. ¡Hola, Cory! ¿Dónde está Chrissy?

translation.en: Now, when you're hunting a ghost, you have to be very quiet.
translation.es: Cuando cazas un fantasma, debes hacerlo muy callado.

translation.en: And what would Madame like to order?
translation.es: ¿Y qué le gustaría pedir a la señora?
Esa es la cara de baño.

translation.en: [Mama laughs] That's right! And what do puppy cars do?
Now I wonder, who could have made all of this mess?
translation.es: Me pregunto quién pudo hacer este lío.

translation.en: That's still our Chrissy. Well, I think that was all of them.
translation.es: Sigues siéndolo. Bueno, creo que vimos todas.

translation.en: Aw, you excited for Mama and Papa to get home, Cory?
translation.es: ¿Te emociona que vuelvan mamá y papá, Cory?

translation.en: Cory, let them through the door! Here, let me grab your bags, dear.
translation.es: ¡Cory, déjalos pasar! Déjame cargar tus maletas, querido.

translation.en: [Cory] I wanna see! Let me see!
Cory, meet your new baby sister, Chrissy.
translation.es: Cory, te presento a tu hermanita, Chrissy.

translation.en: I'm gonna show her my toys!
[Papa's mom] These really are special times.
And they go by so fast.
Mama go back to work now?
How about I hide and you seek?
translation.es: ¿Qué tal si me escondo y tú buscas?
